(Description)
Given a string s, return the longest palindromic substring in s.

--- Solution ---
//Solution for the problem, Longest Palindromic Substring in the leetcode.
class Solution {
    public String longestPalindrome(String s) {
        String longest = "";

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            String odd = expand(s,i,i);
            String even = expand(s,i,i+1);

            if (odd.length() > longest.length()) longest = odd;
            if (even.length() > longest.length()) longest = even;
        }

        return longest;
    }

    private String expand(String s, int left, int right) {
        while (left >= 0 && right < s.length()
            && s.charAt(left) == s.charAt(right)) {
                left--;
                right++;
            }

        return s.substring(left+1, right);
    }
}

--- Approach ---
(Key Concept)
There are two types of palindromic substrings.
1. odd palindrome, 'aba'
2. even palindrome, 'bb'

So that, in this algorithm the loop should be applied into the two cases.
But the common next step is same in here : expanding 1 unit into left and right 
such as, 'a' -> 'bab' & 'bb' -> 'abba'. 

Therefore, in the private it expanded one unit in each left and right.
